features: ['Polyester, Spandex', 'Imported', 'Size: Please refer to the size information in our size chart below the image.', 'Lace Up closure', 'Machine Wash', 'Hoodie are made of polyester and spandex, feel soft and comfortable, breathable and skin-friendly. No peeling, no fading.', 'Our Graphic Hoodies feature a variety of novelty graphics, vibrant and 3d cool designs for you to choose from.', 'Pullover Hoodie features long sleeves, a drawstring hooded neck, print on front and back. And a pocket to hold your cell phone, keys, etc.', 'Hoodies Sweatshirts suitable for unisex adults, men, women, couple and teens. Look great with jeans/pants/trouser/short, etc.', 'Sweatshirt Hoody is great for casual, daily life, sports, work, school, outdoor, travels, vacations and special party wear and so on.']
details: {"Department": "mens", "Date First Available": "June 19, 2022"}
review:
I have the “29 Lyk-blue” color option in this hoodie. That design is a colorful nebula on a black background. The space design starts at the shoulders, goes onto the sleeves, and flows down the body of the hoodie. The back of the hoodie has the same nebula. The hood is plain black; one of the product photos shows the hood as having the design and a different photo shows it as plain black. The hood is lined with black.

The sizing is about an inch smaller than the size chart. I have a size small hoodie. After washing, the chest measurement is approximately 41 inches. The size chart says size small is 42.6 inches. The hoodie narrows at the waist, that measurement is 34 inches.

I usually wear a men’s small in tees and sweatshirts; I expected this hoodie would run small. It fits, but I can feel it pulling at the back if I cross my arms. The hoodie has a little stretch but not a lot. It’s made from a mix of 95% polyester and 5% spandex.

It’s a lightweight hoodie, so it’s not super warm. The material is kind of slick, or maybe slippery is a better way to describe it. It’s not fleecy or sweatshirt material.

The care tag says to hand wash, I don’t know anyone that’s going to hand wash a hoodie. The description says machine wash, and that’s what I did. The hoodie did not shrink in the washer or dryer, and the print didn’t fade at all.

There are a few construction issues on my hoodie. The seams are puckered around the kangaroo pocket, so there’s a permanent wrinkle. The seam on the top of the hood is stretched out, so I can see some of the stitches.

I did not receive any compliments on it the few times I wore it, but I felt comfortable in it. It fits well. Looks good, and for the summer is PERFECT. I wear it usually to services with a maxi skirt and it compliments that nicely. I like the open bat sleeves. Allows you to air out a little if you know what I mean.

Fabric is nice. Does not attract lint excessively. Washes and wears well. Really, no complaints. I am very happy with this. (Also, I removed the tag from this in the video. Tags irritate me.)

features: ['EXCEPTIONAL DURABILITY - Congratulations. You’re about to brandish one of the slickest, strongest buckles on the market. To attach it, just grab a pin, paperclip, or the straight end of a spring bar tool, and release the spring bar through the holes on the sides of the buckle. Then slot the spring bar into the corresponding holes on your watch strap, and you’re done. To remove it, simply reverse the process. Now, you can swap in whatever buckle you’re ready to rock next.', 'THE ARCHER GUARANTEE - Remember when we said our buckles won’t crack, chip, or rust? We meant it. Product Title: Spenco Men's Thrust Slide Sandal
features: ['100% Synthetic', 'Imported', 'Rubber sole', 'Orthotic-grade arch support', 'Deep heel cupping', 'Metatarsal dome', '+5mm heel lift for maximum comfort', 'Ultra-fresh controls smell']
details: {"Department": "mens", "Date First Available": "May 2, 2021", "Manufacturer": "Spenco"}
review:
Update Jan-2019: I wear these daily, almost exclusively indoors, and the sole has hardly any wear. But after approximately a year and half the foam padded insole started to break down in the balls of the feet. I wish the insole had lasted a bit longer, but regardless - I am ordering another pair. I like them that much.

Original Review: The build quality of these sandals is top notch. These aren't cheap rubber sandals. The sole is thick and sturdy.

The padded insole is quite comfortable. And it has good arch, metatarsal and heel support which most sandals lack. So comfy on my relatively flat feet.

My one concern is that the insole's soft memory foam will break down eventually. But that remains to be seen. As it stands right now the insole is like I said, super comfy.

The insole is fabric-covered (unlike most other sandals) and is nice and comfortable. One note: If you plan on wearing the sandals with socks (as I often do, I'll admit!) you will slide around on the insole a bit. So these sandals may be best suited for bare feet.

The only negative is that the sandals (due to their solid build quality) are a bit heavier than any other other sandals I've ever owned. So they take some getting used to with the extra weight on your feet. Sounds trivial, but believe me when you're walking around all day you do notice it. Not a huge issue, but something to note.

Overall though, probably the best built sandals you can buy.

features: ['100% Wool', 'Dry Clean Only', 'Gorgeous wool blend coarse weave outer-shell', 'Elegant oversized hood; Self-tie belt with belt loops', 'Fully Lined; Front concealed pockets', 'Perfect for everyday use as well as for special occasions', 'Product Care: Dry clean only']
details: {"Department": "womens", "Date First Available": "August 30, 2017"}
review: I found this coat to be rather bulky and heavy, literally! I think it weighs 5 or 6 lbs alone! The material is very warm and the waffle weave texture reminds me of my grandma's rug. If you like vintage style, it fits that. Even the buttons remind men of 1970s drawer pulls. However, for me, it was too warm. I live in a warm climate that rarely goes below 50. This coat is more suited to temps in the 30s. The coat is very roomy so has room for sweater layers underneath. I think with a sweater, I could wear this in 20 degrees! It definitely has room for layers and scarves to bundle up! My biggest issue with this coat  though was the hood. It is ridiculously large! Like I could fit two of my head inside of it. It completely engulfed my head. I don't need the purpose for that. It came halfway over my face so with the hood up, I couldnt see.

review:
These joggers are thick and warm. They are made with sweatshirt like fabric. I like these for lounging around but they are too thick and hot to do use while running. However, I can wear them over my gym shorts for running to the gym on cold days.

As far as fit, I got these in a size medium which is what I usually wear. They fit me as I would expect without being too loos or tight. I like that they have a drawstring so I can cinch the waist tighter as needed. There is a knit band around the ankles which keeps these from sliding up. I like these for camping and sitting around the campfire at night when it's a little chilly. Overall, I like these. I'm not totally in love with them. They don't look great, just something to wear around the house.

details: {"Item model number": "GMJ1016-MK", "Department": "Men", "Date First Available": "November 11, 2021"}
review: I should start by saying that the Amazon photos and descriptions are reversed between the Blue and Grey color options for this Alpha Camp Men's Long-Sleeve Hooded Full-Zip Fleece Jacket. I had ordered a Grey color, but received the Blue. The jacket is attractive all the same, so I'm reviewing it as is. My first thoughts are that the jacket is surprisingly lightweight considering its appearance and fleece material. It isn't as warm as thicker polar fleece jackets, but would be suitable for a cool Fall or Spring day, or if you are using it as a layer under a heavier coat during the Winter. Next, the jacket has a generous cut. My husband, who usually wears a large size, tried this men's jacket on and found that the medium size fits him comfortably. Even the sleeves are lengthy enough to suit his long arms. He also likes its appearance and thinks it looks flattering and handsome. This jacket has handy zippered pockets on each side that can fit and secure a mobile phone, keys, and other miscellaneous items. The hood is adequately sized and the front zipper functions well. Overall, this Alpha Camp Men's Long-Sleeve Hooded Full-Zip Fleece Jacket is lightweight, attractive, comfortable, and cut on the larger size. I would order this jacket again.

Product Title: Under Armour Kids' Grade School Pursuit Graphic Sneaker
features: ['Textile', 'Imported', 'Rubber sole', 'Shaft measures approximately low-top from arch', 'Lightweight mesh upper delivers complete breathability', 'Foam padding placed around your ankle collar & under the tongue for an incredibly comfortable fit & feel', 'High rebound, die cut EVA sockliner', 'One piece EVA midsole turns cushioned landings into explosive takeoffs', 'Tire inspired outsole pattern provides ultimate flex & superior traction']
details: {"Item Weight": "6.2 Ounces", "Department": "Unisex-adult", "Date First Available": "November 29, 2018", "Manufacturer": "Under Armour"}
review:
The sneakers are beautifully made. The color combination of light gray fabric, gray shoe laces, gray with black stripes, solid black, with light aqua buttonholes and accent make it a gender-neutral choice. The sole is black patterned rubber which provides a good solid grip and traction. The innersole is apple green and not padded. They are sized pretty true to size.

There is a design element that I find sort of strange—fortunately, it’s just decorative but, initially, it seemed that the heel appears to be slanted outwards. It isn’t. They just made the white outer sole appear thicker on one side and continued the black bottom on the other.

My granddaughter, who has a very high instep, usually only threads the shoe lace through the first four holes. This happens with all brands and this shoe is no exception. She, initially, complained that the padding along the inside from heel to shoe laces made the shoe too tight. The padding is particularly thick at the very back and tapers from there. But, after a few minutes of wear it stopped bothering her and she hasn’t mentioned it since. Her feet are wide and the shoe accommodates her width even with heavy socks on, but it is not specifically a ‘wide’ shoe. Feet of any width will find it a comfortable fit.

These are well made and well styled sneakers suitable for everyday wear and outdoor play.

features: ['UV Protection Coating coating', 'Bridge: 17 millimeters']
details: {"Package Dimensions": "6.93 x 2.68 x 1.61 inches; 3.07 Ounces", "Department": "Unisex-adult", "Date First Available": "November 21, 2020", "Manufacturer": "AMEXI"}
review: Love the classic design and look of these AMEXI Sunglasses!  They will work for either men or women, so that's a big plus.  The one special thing that sets these apart from other sunglasses is the attractive light colored wood ear pieces.  They are curved enough to fit my smaller head, but have enough spring action to fit a larger head.  The frames are basic black with a small silver embellishment on either side at the temple.  The Polarized lens are very nice with that blue-green tint that looks like fly eyes, but a purple tint from the inside, and they have great UV protection.  The construction of the glasses is excellent and very sturdy, as are the hinges holding all together.  The glasses come in a unique wooden box, along with a nice cloth bag for protection, plus a cleaning cloth and tool for adjusting or replacing the screws at the hinges.  All in all, great looking, protective, and fun to wear.

I wouldn’t usually even consider a gray pair of leggings (because I’ve seen them on other women and just feel like they’re a bit too revealing for me) but the charcoal gray style has so much heather/marl pattern I thought they were perfect— stylish and modest coverage!
I’m in between L/XL sizes and I ordered an XL and thought it fit well. They felt like the right size and were very comfortable.
The fit of the leggings is where the love ends for me though. I’m in the process of losing weight and I have a proportional figure but I need compression to feel comfortable. These leggings didn’t have even compression throughout the fabric so they looked awful on me. The waistband is thick and nice compression but where the leg material transitions at the hip it’s not as compressed. So it compressed my midsection and made my hips look a lot fuller than they are in reality (like rubber bands around the middle of a watermelon).
The % of nylon in these leggings gave me an embarrassing camel toe. They need more spandex in the material so the material doesn’t sit in the creases of the groin.
I’m super bummed these didn’t work out. I did return them but I would purchase again from this vendor if they update the products. Even my husband loved the look of them in the package but they just didn’t work for my in-progress body. They look great on already very fit women!

review:
What I got in the mail, was the most disappointing product I’ve ever purchased off Amazon.

First off: the leggings were shipped in the clear plastic bag that normally comes inside another box. Deal-breaker? No, but certainly off-putting.
Immediately they reminded me of those cheap department store leggings from 2015 that you only wore under a skirt because they showed everything with stretch. The only compression I found was in the abdomen- the leg and hip fabric was thin and unflattering. So it makes sense that when I tried the squat test, these leggings failed miserably! Even just holding the fabric up, you could see strange, unattractive ripples in the material.
I don’t know if what I received was a major, yet one-off quality mistake, but this has been my second major issue trying this brand out. Suffice it to say I’m returning these and going back to my trusty Colorfulkoala leggings.

details: {"Is Discontinued By Manufacturer": "No", "Package Dimensions": "7.7 x 4.3 x 1.8 inches; 6.38 Ounces", "Department": "womens", "Date First Available": "July 18, 2017", "Manufacturer": "RONNOX"}
review:
I bought these (solid colored ones) to help with calve tension and tightness that I've experienced for the last year or so. The tightness would be so bad that in the middle of the night, I would get charley horse. I chose these over the socks type as I walk around the house barefoot and am not used to wearing socks in the house. As I'm on the short side, I got the small and they fit me perfectly. I was able to fit them right above my ankles and they come up just underneath my knees with a bit of room to spare (don't over-stretch them). My calve size is on the average to a bit over average (I can zip up knee-high boots, but with no room to spare) and these are not too tight, but I still feel the compression. It's a comfortable feeling. I use them mostly when I go to sleep and sometimes during the daytime. Been using them for a few weeks now and my calves are definitely feeling much better. No longer do I feel like they will cramp up anytime soon.

Cleaning: As with any cloth materials, these do expand a bit after you have been wearing them consistently for a few days. So I've been rotating them every week or so. I wash them with my regular laundry and line dry them. They do go back to the pre-wear state after the wash.
